setup
brew install ruby-install
brew install chruby
ruby-install (find available ruby)
ruby-install ruby <version>
chruby
chruby ruby-2<version>

You should update your gems:
bundle update ffi sassc
They were previously compiled for a different architecture (intel) and now don't run on ARM (M1). Updating them will trigger a new compilation. You can also simply recompile them:
gem pristine ffi sassc


Run dev
jekyll serve (bundle exec serve)

Production bundle
JEKYLL_ENV=production bundle exec jekyll build

Production deploy
git add .
git commit -m "New release"
git push origin master
